          <!-- Section 33 -->
          <div class="mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-4">Section 33 - Approval to host international sports competitions or events</h3>
            
            <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-600">
              <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Section 33 (1)</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Provides that no person may make an offer or offer to host any international sports competition or event in Malaysia without prior written approval from the Minister and the Minister's decision is final.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-red-500">
              <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-red-800">Section 33 (2) - PENALTY</h4>
              <p class="text-red-700">Provides that any person who violates subsection (1) commits an offense and when convicted may be fined <strong>not less than fifty thousand ringgit but not more than five hundred thousand ringgit</strong> or imprisoned for a period <strong>not exceeding five years</strong> or both.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 34 -->
          <div class="mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-4">Section 34 - Use of recognized international methods and guidelines for competitions</h3>
            
            <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-green-600">
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">A sports body must ensure that all competitions and sports events that are authorized, conducted or participated by it and competitions and sports events held under its auspices, follow methods and guidelines recognized by all governing and regulatory bodies for its sports in all matters, including:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 text-gray-700">
                <li>Standards and qualifications of all participants and officials</li>
                <li>Health and safety measures for participants, officials and spectators at the competition or event</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 36 -->
          <div class="mb-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-4">Section 36 - Companies must apply for licenses to operate</h3>
            
            <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-4 border-l-4 border-yellow-500">
              <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Section 36 (1)</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Provides that a company may not engage in any sports activities or in any other activities related to sports, as prescribed by the Minister in regulations, unless it is licensed to do so by the Commissioner.</p>
              
              <div class="bg-orange-100 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-orange-500 mt-4">
                <p class="font-semibold text-orange-800">* IMPORTANT:</p>
                <p class="text-orange-700">Any company (registered under the Companies Act) wishing to organize sports events must be licensed.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-red-500">
              <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-red-800">Section 36 (4) - PENALTY</h4>
              <p class="text-red-700">Provides that any company that violates subsection (1) commits an offense and when convicted may be fined <strong>not less than fifty thousand ringgit but not more than five hundred thousand ringgit</strong> or imprisoned for a period <strong>not exceeding five years</strong> or both.</p>
